  • java.lang.Object
    • de.db.derpate.util.URIParameterEncryptionUtil
  • public final class URIParameterEncryptionUtil

      • encrypt

        public static @NonNull java.lang.String encrypt​(@NonNull java.lang.String parameterValue)
        Returns a hexadecimal representation of the (with global password and salt) AES256 encrypted value.
        This encryption method should be used, when links are visible to the user. The user may copy this link and use it some time later.
        Parameters:
        parameterValue - the value of the parameter to encrypt
        Returns:
        the encrypted value (hex String)

      • encrypt

        public static @NonNull java.lang.String encrypt​(int parameterValue)
        Returns a hexadecimal representation of the (with global password and salt) AES256 encrypted int value.
        This encryption method should be used, when links are visible to the user. The user may copy this link and use it some time later.
        Parameters:
        parameterValue - the int value of the parameter to encrypt
        Returns:
        the encrypted value (hex String)

      • encrypt

        public static @NonNull java.lang.String encrypt​(@NonNull java.lang.String parameterValue,
                                                @NonNull javax.servlet.http.HttpSession session,
                                                @Nullable LoginUser user)
        This static method encrypts the given parameterValue with the HttpSession.getId() as the password and Id.getId() as salt (appending a "0" to the salt, if the number of characters is uneven).
        As a salt, the DEFAULT_SALT will be used. If a LoginUser is set, the id will be appended to the salt.
        Parameters:
        parameterValue - the value of the parameter to encrypt
        session - the HttpSession the client is using
        user - the LoginUser.
        Returns:
        the encrypted value

      • decrypt

        public static @Nullable java.lang.String decrypt​(@Nullable java.lang.String parameterValue)
        Returns the decrypted AES256 value (represented in a base64 format). It must have been encrypted with the global password and salt.
        Parameters:
        parameterValue - the received value of the parameter
        Returns:
        the decrypted value or null, if parameterValue is null or value could not get decrypted
        See Also:
        encrypt(String)

      • decrypt

        public static @Nullable java.util.List<@Nullable java.lang.String> decrypt​(@Nullable java.lang.String[] parameterValues)
        Takes a Array of encrypted AES256 values and returns those, who could get decrypted.
        Useful for the evaluation of http parameters (e.g. for checkboxes).
        Returns null, if parameterValues was null or no value could get decrypted.
        Parameters:
        parameterValues - the received values
        Returns:
        a List of the decryped values (Strings or null, if parameter could not get decrypted), or null, if parameterValues was null

      • decryptToInteger

        public static @Nullable java.lang.Integer decryptToInteger​(@Nullable java.lang.String parameterValue)
        Decryptes the given String, checks if the result is an integer and parses it. If given String is null or not a number, null is returned
        Parameters:
        parameterValue - received value
        Returns:
        decrypted integer or null, if parameterValue was null or not an encrypted integer
